quran[19]{c,v,t}:
  73,1,"O you enwrapped one,"
  73,2,"stand up{1}during the night except a little–",footnotes:1:‘Stand up’ denotes adoration of Allah in night prayers.
  73,3,"for half of it or reduce it a little"
  73,4,"or add to it, and chant the Recital{1}slowly and distinctly.",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is Qur’anwhich literally means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.
  73,5,"Indeed, We are about to cast upon you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>a heavy word."
  73,6,"The vigil of the night is indeed more <span class=""h"">intense<sup foot_note=""81391"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>and more upright for articulation."
  73,7,"Indeed, in the daytime you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>have lengthy work to do."
  73,8,"So remember the Name of your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord and devote yourself to Him with<i class=""s"">(solemn) </i><span class=""h"">devotion.</span>"
  73,9,"<i class=""s"">(He is) </i><span class=""h"">the Lord<sup foot_note=""81392"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>of the East and the West; there is no god but He, so take Him as a Trustee."
  73,10,"And endure patiently what they say, and withdraw from them politely."
  73,11,"And leave to Me the disbelievers, those of luxury, and give them a brief respite."
  73,12,"Indeed, We have shackles and a purgatory"
  73,13,"and food that chokes and a painful punishment"
  73,14,"on the day when the earth and the mountains tremble and the mountains became{1}heaps of sand.",footnotes:1:Frequently the Qur’an addresses the events of the Hereafter in past tense; this grammatical shift should be pondered by the reader.
  73,15,"Indeed, We have sent to you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>a messenger as a witness over you, as We sent to Pharaoh a messenger."
  73,16,"But Pharaoh disobeyed the Messenger, so We seized him with a terrible seizing."
  73,17,"So how, if you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>deny, will you guard yourselves from a day which turns children gray-haired?"
  73,18,"The heaven shatters thereby; His promise has always been fulfilled."
  73,19,"Indeed, this is a reminding, so whoever wills, let him take a way to his Lord."
